name: JUMPING JACKS
description: With hands by side, feet together, quickly jump and bring hands up while landing in a wide stance, then hands back down and feet together. Jumping Jacks are a classic and effective cardiovascular warm-up exercise that engages multiple muscle groups

name: Incline Push-ups
description: Place your hands on an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, with your feet on the ground. Maintain a straight line from head to heels as you lower your chest towards the surface and push back up. This variation targets the upper chest.

name: Push-ups
description: Start in a plank position with hands shoulder-width apart. Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping a straight line from head to heels. Push back up to the starting position. Perform on knees for less intensity.

name: Wide Arm Push-ups
description: Assume a standard push-up position but with your hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart. Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping elbows at a 90-degree angle, and push back up.

name: Declined Push-ups
description: Elevate your feet on an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, while placing your hands on the ground in a push-up position. Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping a straight line from head to heels. Push back up to the starting position.

name: Stretch
description: Lie face down on the floor, place your hands near your shoulders, and push your upper body up while keeping your hips on the ground. Feel the stretch in your chest and hold the position for a duration.
